Package com.iontrading.mkv.messagequeue

Class MkvMQSubscribeConf

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.iontrading.mkv.messagequeue.MkvMQSubscribeConf
  • @Keep
@KeepPublicClassMemberNames
public class MkvMQSubscribeConf
extends Object
    A configuration class for message queue subscriptions.

    This class contains a set of properties which can be passed for customizing subscriptions to message queues created through the MkvMQManager.createSubscription method.

    See Also:
    MkvMQManager, MkvMQ

      • setExpireOnClose

        public final void setExpireOnClose​(boolean expireOnClose)
        Sets the ExpireOnClose value.

        When this value is set to true, the subscription is automatically destroyed as soon as the publisher sets the queue in the CLOSE status.
        Default value is true.

        Parameters:
        expireOnClose - true if the MessageQueue must be automatically destroyed when the remote publisher sets the queue in the CLOSE status.

      • setExpireOnUnpublish

        public final void setExpireOnUnpublish​(boolean expireOnUnpublish)
        Sets the ExpireOnUnpublish value.

        When this value is set to true, the subscription is automatically destroyed as soon as an unpublish event is received for the record which represents the queue.
        Default value is true.

        Parameters:
        expireOnUnpublish - true if the MessageQueue must be automatically destroyed when the remote publisher removes it from the Data Dictionary.

      • setPublisher

        public final void setPublisher​(String publisher)
        Sets the publisher value.

        A message queue subscription can be possibly bound to a certain component. Therefore, when this value is set, subscriptions and ack requests are performed only against the specified publisher.

        Parameters:
        publisher - the name of the publisher component.

      • setTimeout

        public final void setTimeout​(int timeout)
        Sets the Timeout value in seconds.

        The Timeout value defines how long the message queue subscription is to be kept active. When the expiration time is reached the subscription is automatically closed.
        A value of 0 or less makes the subscription to never expire; this is the default.

        Parameters:
        timeout - the timeout value in seconds

      • isCopyStrings

        public final boolean isCopyStrings()
        Returns Whether the underlying MkvUnicodeBuffers of the MQ supply shall be allocated with a new every time by the API, or reused from a pool
        Returns:
        The string memory behavior
        See Also:
        setCopyStrings(boolean)

      • setCopyStrings

        public final void setCopyStrings​(boolean copyStrings)
        Sets the memory allocation behavior for the MQ supply strings If set to true, the API allocates a new MkvUnicodeBuffer for each string fields in incoming MQ supply If set to false, the API reuses the MkvUnicodeBuffers from its own pool Set it to true if you want to process the MQ supplies asynchronously, outside of the notification stack, and do not want to pay for allocating a copy of the strings. By default, the value is false, so the API will reuse the MkvUnicodeBuffers from its own pool, and if you want to process the MQ supplies asynchronously, outside of the notification stack, you must copy the strings in the application code.
        Parameters:
        copyStrings - the desired string memory behavior.
